<chapter xml:id="ch-definite-integrals" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  
  <title>Definite Integrals</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      We begin this chapter by studying the problem of finding the area under a curve.
      The <em>Fundamental Theorem of Calculus</em> describes a surprising connection between this problem and antiderivatives.
      It turns out that antiderivatives are the key to solving the area problem!
    </p>
  </introduction>

